%% UDP <-> WSS fallback timing
%% Source: crates/connector/src/lib.rs
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant NSN as NSN ConnectorManager
    participant Peer as NSGW peer endpoint
    participant Relay as wss://{gw}/relay

    Note over NSN: connect(wg_config) — lib.rs:205

    loop 3 attempts, 3s delay
        NSN->>Peer: UDP 148B probe to peer.endpoint (lib.rs:254)
        alt UDP reachable (any reply or send OK within 5s)
            Peer-->>NSN: reply / send succeeds
            NSN->>NSN: active = Transport::Udp
            Note over NSN: done — TunnelManager drives WG
        else send fails / ICMP unreachable
            Peer-->>NSN: error
        end
    end

    Note over NSN: All 3 UDP attempts failed → fallback

    NSN->>Relay: WSS connect with Bearer token<br/>(tunnel-ws/src/lib.rs:308)
    Relay-->>NSN: 101 Switching Protocols
    NSN->>NSN: active = Transport::Wss(WsTunnel)

    par WSS data-plane
        NSN->>Relay: Message::Binary(WsFrame) * N
        Relay-->>NSN: Message::Binary(WsFrame) * N
    and Periodic upgrade probe (every 300s, lib.rs:328)
        NSN->>Peer: UDP probe
        alt UDP recovered
            Peer-->>NSN: reply
            NSN->>NSN: abort proxy_handle<br/>active = Transport::Udp
            Note over NSN: seamless upgrade WSS → UDP
        else still blocked
            Peer-->>NSN: timeout / err
            Note over NSN: stay on WSS
        end
    end
